.SH NAME
refind-btrfs-snapshots-list-bootsets - List detected boot image sets on the ESP


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBrefind-btrfs-snapshots list bootsets [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Scan the EFI System Partition for boot images and display the detected boot sets.

.PP
Each boot set groups related boot images by kernel name (e.g., "linux", "linux-lts").
A boot set typically contains a kernel, its matching initramfs, an optional fallback
initramfs, and any shared microcode images.

.PP
The command also inspects kernel binaries to extract version strings from their
bzImage headers when possible.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for bootsets

.PP
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	Output in JSON format

.PP
\fB--show-images\fP[=false]
	Show individual boot images in addition to boot sets


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default is /etc/refind-btrfs-snapshots.yaml)

.PP
\fB--local-time\fP[=false]
	Display times in local time instead of UTC

.PP
\fB--log-level\fP="info"
	log level (trace, debug, info, warn, error, fatal, panic)


